1
00:00:20,590 --> 00:00:23,680
There are some things you don't notice when you have them.

2
00:00:26,460 --> 00:00:27,880
Like a huge mansion.

3
00:00:27,880 --> 00:00:30,150
This tea is from the English embassy...

4
00:00:30,150 --> 00:00:33,150
Or the delicious tea cakes made by a chef.

5
00:00:33,150 --> 00:00:36,810
Or the beautiful flower decorations placed by the housekeeper.

6
00:00:36,810 --> 00:00:38,270
Oto.

7
00:00:41,830 --> 00:00:42,780
You look great in that.

8
00:00:42,780 --> 00:00:44,220
Or the people dear to you.

9
00:00:44,220 --> 00:00:47,140
You look wonderful, Oto!

10
00:00:49,920 --> 00:00:53,260
It's a bit too soon to be wearing the uniform.

11
00:00:53,260 --> 00:00:55,110
Nothing wrong with that.

12
00:00:55,110 --> 00:00:57,730
Since you'll need it six months from now. Right?

13
00:00:57,730 --> 00:00:58,860
That's right.

14
00:00:58,860 --> 00:01:02,050
I'm looking forward to seeing your new uniform too, Tenma.

15
00:01:02,050 --> 00:01:04,830
You'll be the first to see it once it arrives.

16
00:01:07,080 --> 00:01:08,340
Mom?

17
00:01:08,340 --> 00:01:10,410
Do you want to rest for a bit?

18
00:01:10,410 --> 00:01:12,500
I'm okay.

19
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:16,100
It's scary how quickly time flies.

20
00:01:16,100 --> 00:01:18,080
I can't believe you two are already going to high school.

21
00:01:18,080 --> 00:01:21,820
Before you know it, you'll be cradling your grandchild.

22
00:01:21,820 --> 00:01:24,010
It does feel that way!

23
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:30,650
I know! Tenma, come and stand next to Oto for a photo.

24
00:01:30,650 --> 00:01:34,110
You don't know what you've got until it's gone.

25
00:01:34,110 --> 00:01:38,820
It means that nothing is guaranteed.

26
00:01:39,470 --> 00:01:45,620
[One year later]
[Present day]

27
00:01:50,770 --> 00:01:53,250
My dad's company went bankrupt

28
00:01:53,250 --> 00:01:56,400
and everything I took for granted collapsed into nothing.

29
00:02:01,980 --> 00:02:06,180
I even cut my hair to save on shampoo.

30
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:13,520
I will have some of that, too.

31
00:02:17,730 --> 00:02:19,980
I'm off.

32
00:02:27,540 --> 00:02:33,120
All that remained was this school uniform.

33
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:35,880
The path I took for granted, was gone.

34
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:41,820
Eitoku Academy, a renowned school with a paved path to prestigious universities that children of the super-rich attend.

35
00:02:41,820 --> 00:02:44,680
During spring vacation, the spa in Bali ー

36
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:46,070
Let's go there sometime.

37
00:02:46,070 --> 00:02:49,770
It's in the Hilton in Cairns.

38
00:02:49,770 --> 00:02:51,300
Hello, Oto!

39
00:02:51,300 --> 00:02:52,460
Hello.

40
00:02:52,460 --> 00:02:54,050
Did you read my message?

41
00:02:54,050 --> 00:02:55,290
Sorry, not yet.

42
00:02:55,290 --> 00:02:57,660
Asami said she found a nice restaurant place.

43
00:02:57,660 --> 00:03:01,060
The parfaits are supposed to be amazing there.

44
00:03:01,060 --> 00:03:02,570
Did you see the photo?
[5,800 yen]

45
00:03:02,570 --> 00:03:04,260
- That's steep!
- Huh?

46
00:03:04,260 --> 00:03:11,780
Oh, uh, steep like a mountain! It looks 50 centimeters tall.

47
00:03:11,780 --> 00:03:14,030
You're hilarious, Oto.

48
00:03:14,030 --> 00:03:16,050
- You should come with us today.
- Today...

49
00:03:16,050 --> 00:03:20,860
I can't let anyone find out about my home and family.

50
00:03:21,490 --> 00:03:25,030
Because...

51
00:03:26,190 --> 00:03:28,840
C5 controls this school.

52
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:34,830
It's a commoner cull!

53
00:03:38,020 --> 00:03:39,850
A commoner cull!

54
00:03:39,850 --> 00:03:42,550
They're about to hunt down commoners!

55
00:03:42,550 --> 00:03:45,890
Someone in this class is gonna get culled for being a commoner.

56
00:03:45,890 --> 00:03:47,640
What?!

57
00:03:48,250 --> 00:03:50,020
It's not me.

58
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:16,990
You're Takuya Komatsubara of Class 2D, right?

59
00:04:16,990 --> 00:04:18,970
Zero donations as of last year.

60
00:04:18,970 --> 00:04:22,980
Class fees are also in arrears.

61
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:26,730
Explain yourself.

62
00:04:31,490 --> 00:04:32,980
My father...

63
00:04:32,980 --> 00:04:37,370
My father's company isn't doing well.

64
00:04:37,370 --> 00:04:39,610
But!

65
00:04:39,610 --> 00:04:41,250
He's currently rebuilding it.

66
00:04:41,250 --> 00:04:44,410
My late school fees should be paid off within half a ye ー

67
00:04:44,410 --> 00:04:47,520
[School Dismissal Notification]

68
00:04:47,520 --> 00:04:51,380
There are no exceptions to commoner culls.

69
00:04:54,090 --> 00:04:56,820
You've soiled the dignity of Eitoku.

70
00:04:56,820 --> 00:05:00,040
- Please listen to ー
- The school doesn't need commoners.

71
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:03,890
Submit your notification to leave the school within 24 hours and be gone.

72
00:05:07,030 --> 00:05:08,700
But...

73
00:05:08,700 --> 00:05:10,370
Wait.

74
00:05:10,370 --> 00:05:12,390
I said, wait!

75
00:05:27,910 --> 00:05:30,350
A friendly reminder to donate, everyone!

76
00:05:30,350 --> 00:05:32,570
If you don't...

77
00:05:32,570 --> 00:05:34,610
You'll be culled as a commoner.

78
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:42,640
You've got some nerve.

79
00:05:42,640 --> 00:05:45,220
How dare you stay at this school when you're a poor peasant.

80
00:05:45,220 --> 00:05:46,520
Hurry up and leave already.

81
00:05:46,520 --> 00:05:49,730
- Yeah, that's right!
- Get out!

82
00:05:49,730 --> 00:05:52,970
A peasant in our new class? Nothing could be worse.

83
00:05:52,970 --> 00:05:54,890
- I know, right?
- Yeah.

84
00:05:54,890 --> 00:05:58,300
I definitely can't let anyone find out...

85
00:05:59,060 --> 00:06:03,420
That I'm a hidden commoner afraid of being culled!

86
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:07,750
- What happened this morning was incredible!
- Sure was...

87
00:06:07,750 --> 00:06:10,600
The righteous quintet who maintain order at Eitoku Academy.

88
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:14,280
Correct 5. Or C5 for short.

89
00:06:14,870 --> 00:06:16,490
Kaito Taira.

90
00:06:16,490 --> 00:06:19,080
Possessor of the highest IQ in all of Eitoku history.

91
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:23,340
And the successor to a family of politicians who have shaped Japan.

92
00:06:25,450 --> 00:06:27,510
Airi Maya.

93
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:31,000
The daughter of a real estate mogul

94
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:34,400
and blessed with looks and charm.

95
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:40,050
Issa Narumiya.

96
00:06:40,890 --> 00:06:43,030
Heir to the Narumiya family,

97
00:06:43,030 --> 00:06:45,370
a powerhouse in the flower arrangement world.

98
00:06:50,340 --> 00:06:52,390
Eibi Sugimaru.

99
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:57,680
Son of the esteemed family that owns the sporting brand EIBI,

100
00:06:57,680 --> 00:07:00,320
and a candidate to compete in the next Olympics.

101
00:07:02,150 --> 00:07:07,050
And the best of them all is the leader himself...

102
00:07:07,050 --> 00:07:09,770
The eminent Haruto Kaguragi!

103
00:07:18,270 --> 00:07:21,720
A genius who's adept at all sports and can speak seven languages.

104
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:22,780
- You're a genius.
- Thank you.

105
00:07:22,780 --> 00:07:24,250
- You're a genius.
- Thank you.

106
00:07:24,250 --> 00:07:25,530
- You're a genius.
- Thank you.

107
00:07:25,530 --> 00:07:27,350
- You're a genius.
- Thank you.

108
00:07:27,350 --> 00:07:28,550
- You're a genius.
- Thank you.

109
00:07:28,550 --> 00:07:30,090
- You're a genius.
- Thank you.

110
00:07:30,090 --> 00:07:34,770
And not to mention how dreamy his face is!

111
00:07:35,670 --> 00:07:39,820
His father is the CEO of Kaguragi Holdings, one of the Big Three Japanese Conglomerates,

112
00:07:39,820 --> 00:07:42,610
alongside Domyoji Group.

113
00:07:42,610 --> 00:07:48,200
He's ranked in "The 100 Most Influential People" in the World for ten years running!

114
00:07:50,300 --> 00:07:54,080
Hey, are you really not going to join us for parfaits?

115
00:07:54,080 --> 00:07:55,430
Sorry, I'll see you next time.

116
00:07:55,430 --> 00:07:58,760
Your father must have it tough with his chauffeur taking time off and all.

117
00:07:58,760 --> 00:07:59,900
I'm home!

118
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:01,920
- Goodbye!
- Goodbye!

119
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:04,150
Goodbye!

120
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:06,410
Goodness. Excuse me!

121
00:08:06,410 --> 00:08:09,530
- Do you have some sort of business being here?
- No, sorry!

122
00:08:10,550 --> 00:08:13,660
I managed to survive another day!

123
00:08:15,190 --> 00:08:17,250
I don't really want to be sneaking around like this.

124
00:08:17,250 --> 00:08:19,180
But... No, stop those thoughts.

125
00:08:19,180 --> 00:08:22,330
I'll be the next victim of commoner culling if I stand out.

126
00:08:22,330 --> 00:08:25,530
I need to stay in the academy, no matter what!

127
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:29,600
No way.

128
00:08:43,710 --> 00:08:45,040
Hey.

129
00:08:47,730 --> 00:08:49,850
Are you trying to kill yourself?

130
00:08:58,520 --> 00:09:01,890
[Hana Sugisaki as Oto Edogawa]

131
00:09:03,150 --> 00:09:06,880
[Sho Hirano as Haruto Kaguragi]

132
00:09:08,250 --> 00:09:11,100
[Taishi Nakagawa as Tenma Hase]

133
00:09:15,740 --> 00:09:20,650
[Boys Over Flowers Season 2]

134
00:09:20,650 --> 00:09:23,670
[Boys Over Flowers Season 2]
[Episode 1]

135
00:09:24,020 --> 00:09:27,830
No way, no way, no way!

136
00:09:30,130 --> 00:09:31,650
Hey, you're wearing our school's uniform.

137
00:09:31,650 --> 00:09:33,980
C5?

138
00:09:35,230 --> 00:09:36,920
Are you hurt?!

139
00:09:36,920 --> 00:09:38,500
Hey, you listening?

140
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:40,330
No!

141
00:09:40,330 --> 00:09:44,180
By "no", I mean that I'm not injured.

142
00:09:44,180 --> 00:09:45,840
Hey, what's your name?

143
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:47,810
Um...

144
00:09:50,610 --> 00:09:53,090
Oto Edogawa from Class 2D.

145
00:09:53,090 --> 00:09:56,260
Daughter of the CEO of the cosmetic brand, Edo Quality, eh?

146
00:09:56,260 --> 00:09:59,090
Haven't you heard of the Personal Data Privacy Act?!

147
00:09:59,090 --> 00:10:01,230
Edo Quality?

148
00:10:01,750 --> 00:10:03,290
My apologies for causing such strife!

149
00:10:03,290 --> 00:10:05,140
I will excuse myself now!

150
00:10:05,140 --> 00:10:06,430
You're leaving on foot?

151
00:10:06,430 --> 00:10:09,650
My chauffeur has a cold!

152
00:10:09,650 --> 00:10:10,980
Bye!

153
00:10:12,580 --> 00:10:13,950
Impressive legs!

154
00:10:13,950 --> 00:10:15,600
Sorry! Excuse me!

155
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:17,430
What's her deal?

156
00:10:23,390 --> 00:10:27,760
That shaved years off my life...

157
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:29,280
How cruel.

158
00:10:29,280 --> 00:10:31,930
They didn't have to yell at me like that.

159
00:10:31,930 --> 00:10:35,580
I thought my heart was going to stop.

160
00:10:35,580 --> 00:10:38,330
How many times have you failed at a part-time job interview now?

161
00:10:38,330 --> 00:10:40,970
But I'm not in the wrong here.

162
00:10:40,970 --> 00:10:43,730
All I did was ask a question.

163
00:10:43,730 --> 00:10:48,380
"Did you perhaps forget a zero or two for this hourly rate?"

164
00:10:52,870 --> 00:10:54,430
Okay.

165
00:10:54,430 --> 00:10:56,280
You don't have to push yourself like this.

166
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:58,210
I'll do what I can.

167
00:10:58,210 --> 00:10:59,660
I'm sorry.

168
00:10:59,660 --> 00:11:05,050
We just need to endure this until you turn 18.

169
00:11:05,050 --> 00:11:08,600
A little over six months has passed since Edo Quality went bankrupt.

170
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:10,090
[Pea sprout soup]

171
00:11:10,090 --> 00:11:11,080
[Bread crust gratin-style casserole]

172
00:11:11,080 --> 00:11:14,570
My mom was brought up in a rich family.

173
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:20,180
The shock from having her mansion and almost all of her possessions taken away,

174
00:11:21,730 --> 00:11:25,460
and loneliness without my dad who's out on a fishing boat to earn money for the family,

175
00:11:25,460 --> 00:11:27,920
have driven her into a deep depression.

176
00:11:27,920 --> 00:11:33,190
Perhaps Makoto is out around the Indian Ocean right now...

177
00:11:34,070 --> 00:11:36,210
I'm off.

178
00:11:36,210 --> 00:11:39,040
Hm? You're going out somewhere, Oto?

179
00:11:41,190 --> 00:11:44,410
How many shifts do you have a week, Oto?

180
00:11:44,410 --> 00:11:45,940
Five.

181
00:11:45,940 --> 00:11:48,140
Whoa, you're working way too much.

182
00:11:48,140 --> 00:11:50,450
Doesn't that weird your friends out?

183
00:11:50,450 --> 00:11:53,090
I haven't told them that I've got a part-time job.

184
00:11:53,090 --> 00:11:55,920
I'd be culled in an instant if anyone ever found out.

185
00:11:55,920 --> 00:11:59,240
You need to have a breather every once in a while.

186
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:00,270
Uh, stop.

187
00:12:00,270 --> 00:12:03,810
- Mr. Maeno?
- Such a cute reaction.

188
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:05,840
Oto-cchi!

189
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:07,590
Come over here!

190
00:12:08,180 --> 00:12:09,610
Okay!

191
00:12:11,910 --> 00:12:13,590
Oto! Over here!

192
00:12:13,590 --> 00:12:16,680
- You're a lifesaver!
- Just ignore Maeno, seriously.

193
00:12:16,680 --> 00:12:19,380
More importantly, look over there!

194
00:12:19,380 --> 00:12:22,050
Megurin in the flesh!

195
00:12:22,050 --> 00:12:26,460
I have to go. I don't have time to be standing around here!

196
00:12:26,460 --> 00:12:28,550
Cut!

197
00:12:28,550 --> 00:12:30,620
Her face is only this big!

198
00:12:30,620 --> 00:12:33,560
I wonder what they're filming. A movie? Or maybe a TV series?

199
00:12:33,560 --> 00:12:35,360
Is she popular?

200
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:37,150
Did you seriously just ask that?

201
00:12:37,150 --> 00:12:39,760
You haven't seen her on smartphone ads?

202
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:42,760
She's the Number One face that teens aspire to have.

203
00:12:42,760 --> 00:12:48,040
And she's always featured on TV as someone with lots of Instagram followers!

204
00:12:48,510 --> 00:12:51,240
What a drag.

205
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:55,560
I thought you'd cheer up if you saw Megurin.

206
00:12:55,560 --> 00:12:56,510
What?

207
00:12:56,510 --> 00:12:59,470
I mean, you seem really down today.

208
00:12:59,470 --> 00:13:02,180
Problems with your mom again?

209
00:13:02,180 --> 00:13:04,700
- No, it's nothing.
- Another take!

210
00:13:04,700 --> 00:13:07,020
Quiet, please!

211
00:13:10,410 --> 00:13:14,260
You should wave to her too, and soak up her beauty vibes!

212
00:13:16,970 --> 00:13:19,170
She's so cute!

213
00:13:19,170 --> 00:13:21,970
Oto! Where are the packages for the customers again?

214
00:13:21,970 --> 00:13:23,780
I'll be there right away.

215
00:13:25,350 --> 00:13:29,220
Maeno's so useless.

216
00:13:30,430 --> 00:13:35,270
Do you know how much the number of students at Eitoku Academy have dropped this past decade?

217
00:13:35,270 --> 00:13:36,880
Twenty percent.

218
00:13:36,880 --> 00:13:39,960
Kaito, there's no fighting the low-birthrate trend.

219
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:41,710
That's not a good enough excuse.

220
00:13:41,710 --> 00:13:48,380
The nearby Momonozono Academy has increased its student count by 38% in only two years.

221
00:13:48,380 --> 00:13:50,570
Their growth is way too quick, no?

222
00:13:50,570 --> 00:13:52,110
It's the work of Tenma Hase.

223
00:13:52,110 --> 00:13:54,300
I know him.

224
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:58,930
He was elected as Student Council President in his first year, and controls the school, right?

225
00:13:58,930 --> 00:14:05,290
His father is the CEO of the IT company, Hase Live, which was listed on the Tokyo Stock Exchange.

226
00:14:05,290 --> 00:14:07,900
Tenma, himself, is talented in both school and sports,

227
00:14:07,900 --> 00:14:10,500
and has garnered popularity of unprecedented levels.

228
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:13,720
Right then, let's begin the regular meeting.

229
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:17,340
A number of Eitoku students have transferred there.

230
00:14:17,340 --> 00:14:19,870
- What?
- Forget about donations.

231
00:14:19,870 --> 00:14:22,160
The scum who don't pay their school fees

232
00:14:22,160 --> 00:14:25,700
are tarnishing the Eitoku brand.

233
00:14:25,700 --> 00:14:28,880
These are your two packages for today, correct?

234
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:30,080
Yes.

235
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:33,870
"Grow Super Tall While You Sleep Z."

236
00:14:33,870 --> 00:14:38,070
"Power Stone: A Belly-Button Plug to Capture Happiness."

237
00:14:38,070 --> 00:14:40,160
I have received my packages in full.

238
00:14:40,160 --> 00:14:42,250
Thank you for your regular patronage.

239
00:14:42,250 --> 00:14:43,930
Look at this.

240
00:14:43,930 --> 00:14:46,390
For the year 2016.

241
00:14:46,390 --> 00:14:48,990
I've compiled the data on the quality of both schools.

242
00:14:48,990 --> 00:14:53,050
The number of students, donation totals, and public opinion.

243
00:14:53,050 --> 00:14:57,490
Eitoku dominated in all aspects for a long time.

244
00:14:57,490 --> 00:15:00,270
However, this is the data for 2017,

245
00:15:01,220 --> 00:15:04,660
and this is now.

246
00:15:04,660 --> 00:15:07,410
The difference between our two schools is paper thin.

247
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:14,380
Eitoku will no longer be unrivaled the moment Momonozono surpasses us.

248
00:15:14,380 --> 00:15:18,780
In other words, Momonozono will seize our title as the supreme school.

249
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:25,500
We created all of this so that wouldn't happen, right?

250
00:15:25,500 --> 00:15:29,330
C5. The righteous quintet.

251
00:15:29,330 --> 00:15:32,840
These black jackets are filled with our firm resolve!

252
00:15:32,840 --> 00:15:36,120
If the dignity of the school drops any further...

253
00:15:36,120 --> 00:15:39,100
we won't be able to show our faces to them.

254
00:15:45,490 --> 00:15:48,990
But I told you to leave the housework to me.

255
00:15:48,990 --> 00:15:52,050
It'll take three days if I leave it to you, Mom.

256
00:15:52,050 --> 00:15:54,260
I can do laundry!

257
00:15:54,260 --> 00:15:56,710
If I have about five hours.

258
00:15:56,710 --> 00:15:59,460
Five hours?

259
00:16:01,490 --> 00:16:06,820
This came while you were at work, Oto.

260
00:16:08,750 --> 00:16:10,780
Ta-da!

261
00:16:10,780 --> 00:16:15,130
The thing I'm looking forward to every month!

262
00:16:16,410 --> 00:16:18,580
Look!

263
00:16:19,100 --> 00:16:20,450
It's beautiful, isn't it?

264
00:16:20,450 --> 00:16:23,600
You have such a lovely fiancé.

265
00:16:24,130 --> 00:16:25,250
I do.

266
00:16:25,250 --> 00:16:29,400
Madam? You have a call from Ms. Edogawa.

267
00:16:35,220 --> 00:16:36,610
Hello?

268
00:16:36,610 --> 00:16:39,460
My apologies for interrupting your busy schedule.

269
00:16:39,460 --> 00:16:43,100
This is Yukie, Oto's mother.

270
00:16:43,100 --> 00:16:48,400
Thank you very much for the lovely present this month as well.

271
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:51,000
I am handing the phone over to Oto now.

272
00:16:51,690 --> 00:16:55,290
Hello? Thank you very much for your constant kind consideration.

273
00:16:55,290 --> 00:16:57,560
You don't need to pay such mind to it.

274
00:16:57,560 --> 00:16:59,450
Why don't you have her give the phone to Tenma?

275
00:16:59,450 --> 00:17:03,740
Sorry. Tenma's at school now.

276
00:17:03,740 --> 00:17:07,320
Then please send Tenma my regards.

277
00:17:07,320 --> 00:17:10,420
I shall do just that.

278
00:17:10,420 --> 00:17:15,530
My engagement to Tenma still stands, despite what's happened to my family.

279
00:17:15,530 --> 00:17:19,590
It was part of Tenma's mother's dying wishes.

280
00:17:19,590 --> 00:17:22,990
On the condition that...

281
00:17:22,990 --> 00:17:27,650
I stay enrolled in Eitoku Academy until I turn 18.

282
00:17:27,650 --> 00:17:31,350
This engagement is my family's only light of hope.

283
00:17:31,350 --> 00:17:35,410
Well, it was, but...

284
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:40,860
What's the matter, Rie?

285
00:17:40,860 --> 00:17:43,120
No, nothing in particular.

286
00:17:43,680 --> 00:17:45,960
Let's have breakfast.

287
00:17:46,480 --> 00:17:47,850
Okay.

288
00:18:10,110 --> 00:18:11,600
Oh.

289
00:18:13,100 --> 00:18:15,570
She appears to be back.

290
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:33,320
It has been a long time since everyone has been present.

291
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:38,470
The two of you have been so busy with business trips.

292
00:18:38,470 --> 00:18:41,420
I'll be away for a while again as of today.

293
00:18:41,420 --> 00:18:44,180
I'll be flying to Seattle this afternoon, so if you need anything ー

294
00:18:44,180 --> 00:18:46,470
"Tell Kobayashi."

295
00:18:46,470 --> 00:18:48,220
Right?

296
00:18:48,220 --> 00:18:49,630
Yes.

297
00:18:53,330 --> 00:18:55,600
Have you heard?

298
00:18:55,600 --> 00:19:00,520
Master was victorious in the tournament last week.

299
00:19:00,520 --> 00:19:02,070
At a national tournament?

300
00:19:02,070 --> 00:19:04,990
No. At a Kanto-region tournament.

301
00:19:09,360 --> 00:19:11,000
Haruto.

302
00:19:12,290 --> 00:19:13,300
Yes?

303
00:19:13,300 --> 00:19:16,090
Do you know why I let you do what you want

304
00:19:16,090 --> 00:19:18,430
without interference?

305
00:19:18,430 --> 00:19:21,130
Because it's a test to determine whether my words,

306
00:19:21,130 --> 00:19:25,040
actions, and everything else are appropriate for this family.

307
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:26,720
Yes.

308
00:19:28,780 --> 00:19:32,370
Don't forget that you bear the Kaguragi name.

309
00:19:32,370 --> 00:19:35,320
I don't need...

310
00:19:35,320 --> 00:19:37,050
imperfect individuals.

311
00:19:48,990 --> 00:19:50,640
Get me a Jaeger-LeCoultre.

312
00:19:50,640 --> 00:19:52,730
As you wish.

313
00:19:55,960 --> 00:19:58,390
- What did the client say?
- Bring the car around.

314
00:19:58,390 --> 00:20:00,160
- Very well.
- Got it.

315
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:02,280
I'll speak to them directly later, then.

316
00:20:02,280 --> 00:20:05,340
Shift the 10AM meeting to 4PM.

317
00:20:18,450 --> 00:20:20,410
I'm disappointed in you.

318
00:20:20,410 --> 00:20:23,410
I only need...

319
00:20:23,410 --> 00:20:24,980
a perfect son.

320
00:20:36,610 --> 00:20:39,650
I managed to get through another day.

321
00:20:39,650 --> 00:20:42,160
I need to be careful so I don't alert C5.

322
00:20:42,160 --> 00:20:43,950
Care to join us and study at Momonozono?

323
00:20:43,950 --> 00:20:45,770
The gates of our school are always open.

324
00:20:45,770 --> 00:20:47,240
Are you dissatisfied with Eitoku?

325
00:20:47,240 --> 00:20:48,730
Please at least take this pamphlet.

326
00:20:48,730 --> 00:20:50,190
Go on.

327
00:20:50,700 --> 00:20:51,950
[Autonomy and Dignity for Students]

328
00:20:51,950 --> 00:20:54,530
Tenma's incredible.

329
00:20:54,530 --> 00:20:57,250
Don't take that trash!

330
00:21:06,360 --> 00:21:08,410
Tell Tenma Hase

331
00:21:08,410 --> 00:21:13,630
that he won't leave unscratched if he ever appears before me after all these dirty tactics.

332
00:21:13,630 --> 00:21:15,570
Ignore this filth!

333
00:21:15,570 --> 00:21:18,000
Have pride in Eitoku!

334
00:21:22,830 --> 00:21:24,780
My apologies!

335
00:21:24,780 --> 00:21:26,890
- Hey!
- Say, Haruto?

336
00:21:26,890 --> 00:21:28,770
What should we do with these guys?

337
00:21:29,940 --> 00:21:31,350
You're going to settle this with violence?

338
00:21:31,350 --> 00:21:33,220
Depends on you guys.

339
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:37,760
Picking a fight with Eitoku...

340
00:21:40,910 --> 00:21:43,690
Your car is ready.

341
00:21:44,660 --> 00:21:47,670
- Master?
- Momonozono filth...

342
00:21:49,160 --> 00:21:51,990
I won't let you get away with this!

343
00:21:53,140 --> 00:21:56,690
We should probably call it a day.

344
00:21:56,690 --> 00:21:58,380
Okay then, I'll make plans of my own.

345
00:21:58,380 --> 00:21:59,620
Do whatever you want.

346
00:21:59,620 --> 00:22:02,910
Hey. How about we go somewhere for a change of pace?

347
00:22:02,910 --> 00:22:05,480
My dad bought a private beach in the Maldives.

348
00:22:05,480 --> 00:22:07,170
Just go already.

349
00:22:08,170 --> 00:22:10,020
Fine.

350
00:22:17,920 --> 00:22:19,450
Master.

351
00:22:20,120 --> 00:22:22,980
It has arrived.

352
00:22:26,320 --> 00:22:29,870
Then see to it as you usually do.

353
00:22:29,870 --> 00:22:31,660
Very well.

354
00:22:34,620 --> 00:22:37,350
Hey! Kobayashi!

355
00:22:38,160 --> 00:22:42,500
C5 definitely know about me now.

356
00:22:47,310 --> 00:22:49,730
You've gotten really good, Oto.

357
00:22:49,730 --> 00:22:52,960
- Huh?
- At wringing out the rag.

358
00:22:54,600 --> 00:22:57,430
When you first started this job,

359
00:22:57,430 --> 00:23:01,590
you barely knew how to use a rag, let alone wring it.

360
00:23:02,830 --> 00:23:04,060
Not like that.

361
00:23:04,060 --> 00:23:09,600
Or that. Do this and then twist it like this.

362
00:23:09,600 --> 00:23:11,080
Understood.

363
00:23:11,080 --> 00:23:15,280
You threw out rags you'd only used once.

364
00:23:15,280 --> 00:23:19,500
Wow, you did it! Great job!

365
00:23:19,500 --> 00:23:21,870
Thank you so much.

366
00:23:21,870 --> 00:23:25,210
And were surprised to see instant noodles for the first time.
[Rich and Flavorful Chuuka Soba Ramen]

367
00:23:25,210 --> 00:23:27,820
It was so obvious that you had a rich upbringing.

368
00:23:27,820 --> 00:23:29,300
This is food?

369
00:23:29,300 --> 00:23:35,020
- You were all like, "This is food?"
- Please stop reminiscing about the past.

370
00:23:35,020 --> 00:23:38,980
I suppose you're still a rich girl since you go to a prestigious school.

371
00:23:38,980 --> 00:23:41,460
Rich girls don't have part-time jobs.

372
00:23:41,460 --> 00:23:46,660
But your parents are amazing for letting you continue to go there even after the bankruptcy.

373
00:23:46,660 --> 00:23:50,910
Well, there are reasons for that...

374
00:23:50,910 --> 00:23:52,400
Reasons?

375
00:23:52,400 --> 00:23:56,070
I can't possibly tell Konno about the engagement.

376
00:23:56,070 --> 00:23:58,120
- Welcome.
- Welcome.

377
00:23:58,120 --> 00:23:59,930
Um.

378
00:23:59,930 --> 00:24:02,090
I'm here to pick up a package.

379
00:24:02,090 --> 00:24:03,340
Sure.

380
00:24:03,340 --> 00:24:05,070
Ch-Charisma...

381
00:24:05,070 --> 00:24:09,060
Charisma-Boosting Mars Rock, personalized with your full name, right?

382
00:24:09,060 --> 00:24:11,840
- Yes, that's right.
- One moment, please.

383
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:15,560
[Charisma-Boosting Mars Rock]

384
00:24:20,180 --> 00:24:24,040
Hm? Mr. Kobayashi...

385
00:24:25,020 --> 00:24:28,110
Are you perhaps Mr. Kobayashi's grandson?

386
00:24:33,690 --> 00:24:35,450
No way.

387
00:24:39,290 --> 00:24:44,210
Huh? Sir? You've forgotten your package.

388
00:24:44,210 --> 00:24:46,220
Off he goes.

389
00:24:47,040 --> 00:24:48,700
Oto?

390
00:24:54,920 --> 00:24:56,830
- I-I'm a goner.
- I-I'm a goner.

391
00:24:59,900 --> 00:25:01,410
What about Airi?

392
00:25:01,410 --> 00:25:03,990
Don't ever tell her about this.

393
00:25:03,990 --> 00:25:07,690
Think about it. If she found out that he's butting heads with a girl...

394
00:25:07,690 --> 00:25:09,240
It'd be hell.

395
00:25:09,240 --> 00:25:12,410
I just want to disappear and die.

396
00:25:12,410 --> 00:25:14,250
After being seen like that...

397
00:25:14,250 --> 00:25:15,570
A martian rock?

398
00:25:15,570 --> 00:25:18,180
- Charisma?
- Talk about lame.

399
00:25:18,180 --> 00:25:20,190
I can't believe it.

400
00:25:23,520 --> 00:25:26,660
You were too careless.

401
00:25:26,660 --> 00:25:29,970
Who'd expect an Eitoku student to be at a convenience store?!

402
00:25:29,970 --> 00:25:33,910
I even addressed it to "Kobayashi" so I wouldn't get found out.

403
00:25:33,910 --> 00:25:36,180
My deepest apologies.

404
00:25:36,180 --> 00:25:38,570
It was my fault for hurting my back.

405
00:25:38,570 --> 00:25:42,310
No, no, no. You're not to blame at all.

406
00:25:43,130 --> 00:25:45,900
I want a blowgun that can kill people, right now.

407
00:25:45,900 --> 00:25:48,580
I shall procure one at once.

408
00:25:48,580 --> 00:25:50,680
Mr. Kobayashi.

409
00:25:50,680 --> 00:25:53,420
They don't sell things like that.

410
00:25:55,320 --> 00:25:57,660
I shall excuse myself.

411
00:25:59,190 --> 00:26:02,010
What's the deal with today?

412
00:26:02,870 --> 00:26:06,570
I told you not to buy shady things online.

413
00:26:07,690 --> 00:26:09,630
It's not shady!

414
00:26:09,630 --> 00:26:12,980
I've got this that brings happiness if you put it in your belly button!

415
00:26:13,690 --> 00:26:17,570
"Belly-Button Plug to Capture Happiness".

416
00:26:19,370 --> 00:26:23,220
You're putting effort into the wrong places!

417
00:26:23,220 --> 00:26:25,920
Like spreading rumors about you being strong at fighting.

418
00:26:25,920 --> 00:26:28,650
Haruto Kaguragi against five...

419
00:26:28,650 --> 00:26:32,300
Actually... Tweet that I won against 50 hooligans in a fight.

420
00:26:32,300 --> 00:26:33,430
Very well.

421
00:26:33,430 --> 00:26:36,460
[Haruto Kaguragi Won Against 50 Hooligans in a Fight]

422
00:26:36,460 --> 00:26:39,580
Also! Make me a round-up blog.

423
00:26:39,580 --> 00:26:41,490
You can only say "thank you,"

424
00:26:41,490 --> 00:26:44,120
yet you lied that you can speak seven languages.

425
00:26:44,120 --> 00:26:45,550
Xie xie. Gracias.

426
00:26:45,550 --> 00:26:46,560
[Popularity-Boosting Native American Feather]

427
00:26:46,560 --> 00:26:50,440
Buying ridiculous amounts of "lucky" items online.

428
00:26:50,440 --> 00:26:51,990
Master.

429
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:54,910
If you wear these beads,

430
00:26:54,910 --> 00:26:59,200
your wish will come true within eight days.

431
00:26:59,200 --> 00:27:01,220
Buy ten of them.

432
00:27:01,220 --> 00:27:02,950
Shut up.

433
00:27:03,850 --> 00:27:06,860
I'm doing all this to bring myself closer to the level of Domyoji.

434
00:27:06,860 --> 00:27:09,140
Then what about this?

435
00:27:13,650 --> 00:27:17,110
Is this hologram to bring you closer to Domyoji, too?

436
00:27:17,110 --> 00:27:18,560
Well...

437
00:27:18,560 --> 00:27:21,680
I mean, look at how divine it is...

438
00:27:21,680 --> 00:27:25,700
Just gazing upon it purifies your soul.

439
00:27:25,700 --> 00:27:28,070
You're way too obsessed.

440
00:27:28,680 --> 00:27:31,090
I made a promise with Domyoji.

441
00:27:31,090 --> 00:27:32,870
Here we go again.

442
00:27:32,870 --> 00:27:38,540
That's why I need to restore Eitoku to the school that everyone envied, just like how it used to be.

443
00:27:38,540 --> 00:27:39,940
Like when F4 was around.

444
00:27:39,940 --> 00:27:41,720
We will protect Eitoku!

445
00:27:41,720 --> 00:27:45,020
The birth of C5!

446
00:27:51,250 --> 00:27:53,220
Haruto.

447
00:27:53,220 --> 00:27:55,550
If you keep up the hard work,

448
00:27:55,550 --> 00:27:56,940
it will eventually pay off...

449
00:27:56,940 --> 00:28:00,090
Do we have time to be so complacent?

450
00:28:00,090 --> 00:28:03,360
Especially after that hidden commoner saw me like this.

451
00:28:03,360 --> 00:28:04,820
I'm sure tomorrow...

452
00:28:04,820 --> 00:28:06,360
You're pathetic, Kaguragi!

453
00:28:06,360 --> 00:28:08,370
What a loser!

454
00:28:10,200 --> 00:28:11,920
Haruto!

455
00:28:11,920 --> 00:28:12,960
Huh?

456
00:28:12,960 --> 00:28:15,760
If you gently poke around where a commoner is desperately hiding,

457
00:28:15,760 --> 00:28:19,420
you'll find some dust.

458
00:28:23,680 --> 00:28:28,280
I'll be commoner culled for sure after being spotted at work like that.

459
00:28:28,280 --> 00:28:32,270
Martian rocks are this color, huh.

460
00:28:33,660 --> 00:28:37,210
Kaguragi... Hare?
[T/N: "Haruto" can also be read as "Hare"]

461
00:28:37,740 --> 00:28:40,460
Hey! Don't open that without permission!

462
00:28:40,460 --> 00:28:44,880
Huh? Isn't this a present for me?

463
00:28:44,880 --> 00:28:46,000
What makes you think that?

464
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:50,640
My work boss forced this onto me and told me to give it to my friend.

465
00:28:50,640 --> 00:28:55,740
Say, doesn't this rock look like the ring your father bought for me?

466
00:28:55,740 --> 00:28:57,580
You know, the ruby...

467
00:28:57,580 --> 00:28:59,130
Does it?

468
00:28:59,130 --> 00:29:00,890
It does.

469
00:29:00,890 --> 00:29:04,250
That and everything else got taken away.

470
00:29:12,850 --> 00:29:14,210
Hey, Mom?

471
00:29:14,210 --> 00:29:15,620
Yes?

472
00:29:17,150 --> 00:29:18,790
What would happen...

473
00:29:20,430 --> 00:29:24,050
if I stopped going

474
00:29:24,930 --> 00:29:26,620
to Eitoku Academy?

475
00:29:27,640 --> 00:29:29,980
Well...

476
00:29:33,460 --> 00:29:37,350
We'd all have to die as a family.

477
00:29:38,720 --> 00:29:41,030
That's the only path for us.

478
00:29:41,030 --> 00:29:43,020
Talk about overreacting!

479
00:29:43,020 --> 00:29:46,300
Don't say such scary things!

480
00:29:46,300 --> 00:29:47,810
Look.

481
00:29:49,220 --> 00:29:55,040
Your father's doing his best out at sea.

482
00:29:56,110 --> 00:29:59,750
You just need to stick it out until you turn 18.

483
00:29:59,750 --> 00:30:01,360
I can't tell her...

484
00:30:01,360 --> 00:30:05,000
that I'll get a notice to quit school tomorrow.

485
00:30:06,160 --> 00:30:07,600
Right.

486
00:30:08,800 --> 00:30:13,590
I'm going to school just to get culled as a commoner.

487
00:30:14,190 --> 00:30:15,960
Oto.

488
00:30:16,640 --> 00:30:20,430
Sorry for putting you through all of this.

489
00:30:20,430 --> 00:30:25,980
But I want you to return to your old, smiley self

490
00:30:25,980 --> 00:30:31,600
through your engagement with Tenma.

491
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:36,330
That's the least I can do as your mom.

492
00:30:43,120 --> 00:30:44,830
Thanks.

493
00:30:50,350 --> 00:30:53,550
Spare this at the very least, please!

494
00:30:54,340 --> 00:30:55,800
Someone, help!

495
00:30:55,800 --> 00:30:57,290
Mrs. Housekeeper...

496
00:31:05,440 --> 00:31:08,670
My whole life has been turned upside down.

497
00:31:17,830 --> 00:31:20,930
And my fear of being ousted as a commoner in hiding

498
00:31:20,930 --> 00:31:23,490
led me to distance myself from my friends.

499
00:31:24,610 --> 00:31:29,420
I can't go back to the old me anymore.

500
00:31:29,420 --> 00:31:31,140
- Oto Edogawa.
- Huh?

501
00:31:31,140 --> 00:31:33,350
Come with me.

502
00:31:33,350 --> 00:31:36,150
You've got some nerve showing up at school.

503
00:31:37,580 --> 00:31:40,110
Um, I...

504
00:31:40,110 --> 00:31:44,340
Working at a convenience store because your dad's company went bankrupt, eh?

505
00:31:45,640 --> 00:31:49,310
You're worse than a commoner. You're poor.

506
00:31:50,250 --> 00:31:54,500
How dare you boldly lie and sit in school like that.

507
00:31:55,490 --> 00:31:58,470
I have to protect Eitoku.

508
00:31:58,470 --> 00:32:02,570
From sewer rats who try to destroy the dignity of the school.

509
00:32:02,570 --> 00:32:04,460
Don't show your face around here.

510
00:32:07,790 --> 00:32:11,510
We don't need commoners at Eitoku.

511
00:32:25,780 --> 00:32:27,820
Stop!

512
00:32:27,820 --> 00:32:29,400
Haruto!

513
00:32:37,040 --> 00:32:40,470
C'mon, let's have some fun.

514
00:32:40,470 --> 00:32:41,970
Hey!

515
00:32:41,970 --> 00:32:45,030
You should be grateful we approached you!

516
00:32:45,030 --> 00:32:47,970
Pitiful student from a ruined school!

517
00:32:57,510 --> 00:32:59,170
A wall slam? Who does that these days?!

518
00:32:59,170 --> 00:33:01,790
I know, right? I can't believe I did that either!

519
00:33:04,320 --> 00:33:06,620
Quit staring!

520
00:33:08,160 --> 00:33:09,680
I'll call Sugimaru over.

521
00:33:09,680 --> 00:33:10,990
Thanks.

522
00:33:10,990 --> 00:33:13,860
- Hang out with us.
- Sorry, I can't.

523
00:33:16,480 --> 00:33:19,380
Didn't you hear? I said hang out with me!

524
00:33:27,830 --> 00:33:30,070
You're not going to protect her?

525
00:33:33,420 --> 00:33:36,180
You said you'd protect Eitoku.

526
00:33:36,180 --> 00:33:38,960
Yet you're just watching quietly and doing nothing to help.

527
00:33:38,960 --> 00:33:41,800
Shut up, you worthless commoner.

528
00:33:46,710 --> 00:33:48,810
You always act so arrogant and snobby.

529
00:33:48,810 --> 00:33:50,410
Shut up.

530
00:33:51,310 --> 00:33:53,590
What's the point of C5?

531
00:33:53,590 --> 00:33:55,930
What's the point of "Correct 5"?

532
00:33:56,720 --> 00:34:00,970
You don't have the right to call yourself a member of a righteous quintet!

533
00:34:01,950 --> 00:34:05,020
If you have the time to buy such junk, then use it to be a better person.

534
00:34:05,710 --> 00:34:07,850
You're a hopeless joke!

535
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:16,590
We're a little short on money, you know?

536
00:34:16,590 --> 00:34:21,220
This is nothing to a rich Eitoku student like you.

537
00:34:22,040 --> 00:34:23,690
Stop! Please!

538
00:34:23,690 --> 00:34:27,050
Shut up!

539
00:34:28,600 --> 00:34:30,450
Stop it!

540
00:34:30,450 --> 00:34:33,550
- Give that back!
- You've got more?

541
00:34:33,550 --> 00:34:37,370
Honestly. You're a hopeless kid.

542
00:34:50,450 --> 00:34:53,860
Hey, butt out.

543
00:35:21,990 --> 00:35:25,570
You're just going to stand there while one of your friends gets beaten up?

544
00:35:26,660 --> 00:35:30,270
But there's nothing I can do.

545
00:35:30,270 --> 00:35:32,380
Then get stronger.

546
00:35:34,210 --> 00:35:38,750
You have to get stronger to protect what's important to you.

547
00:35:42,860 --> 00:35:45,620
Hey! Stop that!

548
00:35:46,410 --> 00:35:49,420
Look, we've got another girl to play with now!

549
00:35:51,050 --> 00:35:53,580
How long are you going to stand there crying?

550
00:35:53,580 --> 00:35:56,940
I'm going to get stronger.

551
00:35:59,790 --> 00:36:02,980
Eitoku's in your hands.

552
00:36:08,520 --> 00:36:10,310
Get stronger...

553
00:36:22,390 --> 00:36:23,810
Hey!

554
00:36:38,960 --> 00:36:41,630
Get out of here if you don't want to get hurt.

555
00:36:41,630 --> 00:36:43,440
Is he for real?

556
00:36:43,440 --> 00:36:46,660
I'm telling you to stop touching them with your filthy hands.

557
00:36:48,390 --> 00:36:50,220
What's your problem?

558
00:36:55,890 --> 00:37:00,960
I won't let anyone call me "hopeless" ever again...

559
00:37:01,730 --> 00:37:03,750
Never again!

560
00:37:09,670 --> 00:37:12,470
I... I hit him?

561
00:37:22,050 --> 00:37:23,520
Ow!

562
00:37:25,820 --> 00:37:27,420
No way.

563
00:37:27,420 --> 00:37:29,220
Seriously?

564
00:37:30,420 --> 00:37:32,100
Thank goodness.

565
00:37:32,100 --> 00:37:33,890
They just collapsed on their own.

566
00:37:33,890 --> 00:37:36,360
My hand hurts so bad.

567
00:37:36,360 --> 00:37:38,290
I think I might've broken it.

568
00:37:38,290 --> 00:37:39,960
Um.

569
00:37:39,960 --> 00:37:43,900
- Ow!
- Thank you very much, Kaguragi!

570
00:37:43,900 --> 00:37:45,510
What?

571
00:37:45,510 --> 00:37:47,260
Whoa! He took out three guys in one hit!

572
00:37:47,260 --> 00:37:49,670
That's our leader of Eitoku!

573
00:37:50,300 --> 00:37:53,050
This...

574
00:37:55,110 --> 00:37:57,840
Isn't too bad...

575
00:37:57,840 --> 00:37:59,780
In fact, it's awesome!

576
00:38:02,450 --> 00:38:05,200
I'll protect Eitoku Academy.

577
00:38:06,190 --> 00:38:09,510
I, Haruto Kaguragi,

578
00:38:09,510 --> 00:38:12,300
will revive Eitoku Academy!

579
00:38:15,420 --> 00:38:27,380
C5! C5! C5!

580
00:38:27,380 --> 00:38:28,360
Haruto!

581
00:38:28,360 --> 00:38:29,890
What's this?

582
00:38:29,890 --> 00:38:31,440
A miracle.

583
00:38:31,440 --> 00:38:32,680
Kaguragi!

584
00:38:32,680 --> 00:38:33,940
Haruto!

585
00:38:33,940 --> 00:38:35,170
Kaguragi!

586
00:38:35,170 --> 00:38:36,480
Haruto!

587
00:38:36,480 --> 00:38:37,750
Kaguragi!

588
00:38:37,750 --> 00:38:38,990
Haruto!

589
00:38:38,990 --> 00:38:41,900
I forgot about that!

590
00:38:48,800 --> 00:38:52,180
[Let me stay at Eitoku]

591
00:38:58,160 --> 00:39:01,270
[I'll reveal everything if you don't]

592
00:39:06,480 --> 00:39:07,320
[Charisma-Boosting Mars Rock]

593
00:39:07,320 --> 00:39:08,580
Kaguragi!

594
00:39:08,580 --> 00:39:09,880
Haruto!

595
00:39:09,880 --> 00:39:11,230
Kaguragi!

596
00:39:11,230 --> 00:39:12,570
Haruto!

597
00:39:12,570 --> 00:39:13,870
Kaguragi!

598
00:39:13,870 --> 00:39:15,220
Haruto!

599
00:39:15,220 --> 00:39:16,510
Kaguragi!

600
00:39:16,510 --> 00:39:18,050
Haruto!

601
00:39:22,330 --> 00:39:24,210
Crap...

602
00:39:24,210 --> 00:39:25,450
Haruto!

603
00:39:25,450 --> 00:39:29,020
By the way, Haruto, when did you learn how to fight?

604
00:39:29,020 --> 00:39:32,340
It was clearly just a lucky hit.

605
00:39:33,150 --> 00:39:38,010
No matter how uncool you might look, winning is what's most important, according to Kei Nishikori.

606
00:39:43,410 --> 00:39:45,080
Haruto?

607
00:39:45,750 --> 00:39:48,200
That commoner in disguise...

608
00:39:50,470 --> 00:39:54,760
As long as she's around, I can't rule over all

609
00:39:54,760 --> 00:39:56,320
I won't let her get away.

610
00:39:56,320 --> 00:39:58,970
How dare a commoner like her threaten me.

611
00:39:58,970 --> 00:40:01,250
Our enemy's a tough one.

612
00:40:01,250 --> 00:40:03,980
What are you getting all impressed about?

613
00:40:03,980 --> 00:40:09,620
Hey, isn't there any way to keep her mouth shut?

614
00:40:09,620 --> 00:40:11,870
There is.

615
00:40:12,680 --> 00:40:14,480
But it might not be for you.

616
00:40:14,480 --> 00:40:16,350
What? Tell me.

617
00:40:20,350 --> 00:40:24,080
You have to make her yours.

618
00:40:24,080 --> 00:40:27,440
- What?
- A girl would never threaten a boy she's in love with, right?

619
00:40:27,440 --> 00:40:30,220
Don't be ridiculous.

620
00:40:35,850 --> 00:40:39,140
I don't want to blackmail others.

621
00:40:39,140 --> 00:40:41,260
I've got no choice,

622
00:40:41,260 --> 00:40:42,710
but...

623
00:40:42,710 --> 00:40:44,400
Oto?

624
00:40:44,400 --> 00:40:47,580
You were spacing out just now, weren't you?

625
00:40:48,200 --> 00:40:50,010
Sorry.

626
00:40:50,010 --> 00:40:51,910
Your shift's almost over, right?

627
00:40:51,910 --> 00:40:53,680
Let's have dinner together.

628
00:40:54,550 --> 00:40:57,250
My mother is waiting at home with food for me.

629
00:40:57,250 --> 00:40:59,140
Who cares about that?

630
00:40:59,140 --> 00:41:01,090
Maeno?

631
00:41:01,090 --> 00:41:05,230
Don't blame me if the store manager yells at you again.

632
00:41:05,230 --> 00:41:06,930
So you're the one who tattled on me.

633
00:41:06,930 --> 00:41:11,020
Yes and goodbye.

634
00:41:20,360 --> 00:41:21,830
Thank you so much.

635
00:41:21,830 --> 00:41:25,010
Hey, why don't we grab a quick coffee after your shift?

636
00:41:25,010 --> 00:41:27,210
- What?
- For a change of pace.

637
00:41:27,210 --> 00:41:30,230
You've already cooked for your mom, right?

638
00:41:30,960 --> 00:41:33,460
But money's a bit tight this month...

639
00:41:33,460 --> 00:41:36,320
It's my treat.

640
00:41:36,320 --> 00:41:39,050
- But...
- You have nothing to fear.

641
00:41:39,050 --> 00:41:40,240
Ta-da!

642
00:41:40,240 --> 00:41:43,960
Look! A free drink of your choice!

643
00:41:43,960 --> 00:41:45,930
Neat, right?

644
00:41:47,440 --> 00:41:49,580
I don't know what's eating at you right now,

645
00:41:49,580 --> 00:41:53,190
and I might not be the most reliable person,

646
00:41:53,190 --> 00:41:55,850
but I'm here to lend an ear whenever you need it.

647
00:41:57,030 --> 00:41:59,000
Konno...

648
00:42:03,660 --> 00:42:05,390
Hey, you.

649
00:42:06,630 --> 00:42:07,510
What?

650
00:42:07,510 --> 00:42:10,980
Y-You got some time after this?

651
00:42:11,970 --> 00:42:14,860
- Excuse me?
- Of course you've got nothing to do.

652
00:42:14,860 --> 00:42:16,590
You're a commoner, after all.

653
00:42:22,690 --> 00:42:23,970
Let's go.

654
00:42:23,970 --> 00:42:25,700
Uh.

655
00:42:25,700 --> 00:42:27,380
Where?

656
00:42:27,380 --> 00:42:29,350
Where else?

657
00:42:29,350 --> 00:42:31,010
My place.

658
00:42:31,010 --> 00:42:32,790
What?!

659
00:42:41,420 --> 00:42:43,650
No way! Why?!

660
00:42:43,650 --> 00:42:46,820
Wow! This is amazing!

661
00:42:46,820 --> 00:42:49,230
I can't believe this!

662
00:42:49,980 --> 00:42:51,750
Chandeliers!

663
00:42:51,750 --> 00:42:53,880
This is incredible!

664
00:42:53,880 --> 00:42:55,720
Unreal!

665
00:42:55,720 --> 00:43:00,020
This is totally like "Gossip Girl"!

666
00:43:00,620 --> 00:43:02,600
Oh my gosh!

667
00:43:02,600 --> 00:43:04,080
Guess I'm leaving, after all.

668
00:43:04,080 --> 00:43:07,120
Huh? Why? Please!

669
00:43:07,120 --> 00:43:11,410
Please wait just a little longer. I want to take a photo for my Instagram.

670
00:43:12,810 --> 00:43:15,460
I should have refused him right there and then.

671
00:43:15,460 --> 00:43:17,560
The two of us would love to go!

672
00:43:17,560 --> 00:43:21,810
Come on! Just think of it as a free meal!

673
00:43:21,810 --> 00:43:23,510
Still...

674
00:43:23,510 --> 00:43:25,130
Hey.

675
00:43:25,130 --> 00:43:26,710
What are you doing?

676
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:38,600
Why are you in a tuxedo?

677
00:43:38,600 --> 00:43:41,980
- Why not? This is how I usually dress.
- Holy cow.

678
00:43:42,510 --> 00:43:44,400
Seriously, the camera loves you!

679
00:43:44,400 --> 00:43:48,520
You'd totally be a prince if you had a horse next to you.

680
00:43:48,520 --> 00:43:49,550
Come with me.

681
00:43:49,550 --> 00:43:52,460
Will do! Right behind you!

682
00:43:53,100 --> 00:43:54,980
Picture perfect.

683
00:43:54,980 --> 00:43:57,360
So cool!

684
00:44:02,520 --> 00:44:04,500
Where are we?

685
00:44:06,400 --> 00:44:07,940
Something's there.

686
00:44:07,940 --> 00:44:09,820
I can see something.

687
00:44:11,940 --> 00:44:14,030
Gosh, what's all of this?!

688
00:44:16,560 --> 00:44:17,570
Wow!

689
00:44:17,570 --> 00:44:20,880
What do you think? A commoner wouldn't be able to pull this off, right?

690
00:44:20,880 --> 00:44:24,200
What? This is all for Oto-cchi?

691
00:44:24,200 --> 00:44:27,010
That's what I said.

692
00:44:27,010 --> 00:44:30,540
I mean, this is just an average day for me.

693
00:44:32,090 --> 00:44:33,990
What do you think, Edogawa?

694
00:44:34,990 --> 00:44:36,600
It's impressive.

695
00:44:36,600 --> 00:44:38,030
I know, right?

696
00:44:39,380 --> 00:44:40,910
Welcome.

697
00:44:40,910 --> 00:44:43,420
Thank you for blessing us with your presence.

698
00:44:43,420 --> 00:44:45,540
Please collect their belongings.

699
00:44:45,540 --> 00:44:48,170
You live here, Mr. Kobayashi?

700
00:44:48,170 --> 00:44:50,660
I am a butler here.

701
00:44:50,660 --> 00:44:57,050
I would like to thank you for all of the kindness you have shown me.

702
00:44:57,050 --> 00:44:58,750
It's a pleasure.

703
00:44:58,750 --> 00:45:03,780
Please enjoy yourselves tonight to your heart's content.

704
00:45:03,780 --> 00:45:06,630
- I will!
- Do make yourselves at home.

705
00:45:09,990 --> 00:45:12,260
Oh my gosh!

706
00:45:14,140 --> 00:45:16,750
Come on, Oto-cchi! Hurry up!

707
00:45:16,750 --> 00:45:18,990
Wow!

708
00:45:18,990 --> 00:45:20,250
May I?

709
00:45:20,250 --> 00:45:21,830
Wow, thank you so much!

710
00:45:21,830 --> 00:45:25,570
I don't like the memories this brings back...

711
00:45:30,620 --> 00:45:33,400
I'm sure my mom would be thrilled if she were here.

712
00:45:33,400 --> 00:45:36,340
No way. Are you kidding me?

713
00:45:38,490 --> 00:45:41,710
There's seriously a horse here!

714
00:45:44,620 --> 00:45:46,740
Good little horsey. You're so cute!

715
00:45:46,740 --> 00:45:49,660
Come, Oto-cchi! Give it a pat.

716
00:45:49,660 --> 00:45:50,690
Go on.

717
00:45:50,690 --> 00:45:52,470
Of course I have a horse.

718
00:45:52,470 --> 00:45:54,020
Good horsey!

719
00:45:54,020 --> 00:45:56,340
Wow!

720
00:46:07,760 --> 00:46:09,350
Such a poor peasant.

721
00:46:09,350 --> 00:46:15,820
Oh my gosh! Princes really do exist, Oto-cchi!

722
00:46:15,820 --> 00:46:18,150
I guess they do.

723
00:46:18,150 --> 00:46:20,990
Whoa! What's with that chunk of meat?!

724
00:46:20,990 --> 00:46:23,590
Just as planned.

725
00:46:28,800 --> 00:46:33,070
What's with this meat?! It melts in your mouth!

726
00:46:33,070 --> 00:46:35,860
It's the highest grade, A5-ranked meat.

727
00:46:35,860 --> 00:46:37,760
Don't eat too much and get indigestion.

728
00:46:37,760 --> 00:46:41,100
What?! Is this caviar?

729
00:46:41,100 --> 00:46:42,530
I've never seen it before!

730
00:46:42,530 --> 00:46:45,480
It's caviar that commoners usually don't get to taste.

731
00:46:45,480 --> 00:46:48,280
It's a limited edition product.

732
00:46:48,280 --> 00:46:52,400
I've eaten so much of it, I'm practically sick of it.

733
00:46:56,550 --> 00:47:00,510
I'm so relieved now!

734
00:47:00,510 --> 00:47:03,500
You actually have friends.

735
00:47:03,500 --> 00:47:06,310
Friends who'll do such wonderful things for you!

736
00:47:06,310 --> 00:47:07,780
No, we're not frie -

737
00:47:07,780 --> 00:47:10,660
Hey! Please stick by Oto-cchi, okay?

738
00:47:10,660 --> 00:47:14,080
- Konno, please!
- She's such a good girl!

739
00:47:14,080 --> 00:47:18,080
Her family's going through hard times, but she cuts costs where she can and doesn't complain.

740
00:47:18,080 --> 00:47:19,670
- And...
- It's really okay.

741
00:47:19,670 --> 00:47:22,230
Pitiful peasants.

742
00:47:22,880 --> 00:47:25,770
Hm? What did you say just now?

743
00:47:34,750 --> 00:47:37,070
I'm so sorry.

744
00:47:37,070 --> 00:47:39,940
W-W-What do I do?!

745
00:47:39,940 --> 00:47:43,670
- Gosh, what do I do?!
- Calm down.

746
00:47:45,720 --> 00:47:47,550
I'm so sorry.

747
00:47:52,440 --> 00:47:56,430
U-Um, I'll pay for everything.

748
00:47:56,430 --> 00:47:57,810
Your clothes, and your plate...

749
00:47:57,810 --> 00:47:59,680
A million yen.

750
00:47:59,680 --> 00:48:03,580
- What?
- That's about how much it costs...

751
00:48:03,580 --> 00:48:06,140
for this custom-made tuxedo, shirt, and shoes.

752
00:48:06,140 --> 00:48:09,580
As for the limited edition Okura Art China plate...

753
00:48:09,580 --> 00:48:10,940
- Kato.
- Yes?

754
00:48:10,940 --> 00:48:13,370
How much would it cost to replace the set?

755
00:48:13,370 --> 00:48:16,420
Approximately 10 million yen.

756
00:48:16,420 --> 00:48:18,160
What?

757
00:48:18,160 --> 00:48:20,080
Do you have the money for that?

758
00:48:21,800 --> 00:48:23,880
You can't pay, can you?

759
00:48:24,700 --> 00:48:27,000
Not straight away...

760
00:48:27,000 --> 00:48:30,350
But I will pay you back, bit by bit!

761
00:48:31,040 --> 00:48:32,390
Excuse me?

762
00:48:32,390 --> 00:48:34,870
How many centuries will that take?

763
00:48:38,000 --> 00:48:41,960
For a commoner like you collecting menial things like this.

764
00:48:50,710 --> 00:48:53,260
You got carried away, didn't you?

765
00:48:54,150 --> 00:48:57,690
This place is worlds apart from the land of commoners.

766
00:48:59,020 --> 00:49:01,760
I suppose I pity you.

767
00:49:02,730 --> 00:49:07,270
Because it's not like you wanted to be born into a family of commoners.

768
00:49:07,270 --> 00:49:08,990
Relax.

769
00:49:08,990 --> 00:49:11,480
I won't make you pay for this.

770
00:49:13,530 --> 00:49:16,570
Because you're a friend of Edogawa's.

771
00:49:16,570 --> 00:49:18,900
I'll make an exception for you.

772
00:49:18,900 --> 00:49:21,110
Because I'm generous.

773
00:49:21,110 --> 00:49:24,150
Unlike you narrow-minded commoners.

774
00:49:33,560 --> 00:49:35,250
Are you okay?

775
00:49:37,350 --> 00:49:39,320
- Call Mr. Kobayashi.
- Right away.

776
00:49:42,020 --> 00:49:44,950
I don't care what you say about me.

777
00:49:44,950 --> 00:49:49,230
It's true that I'm deceiving everyone at school, and that I'm a commoner in disguise.

778
00:49:50,490 --> 00:49:55,010
But I won't let you hurt Konno!

779
00:49:55,010 --> 00:49:57,010
Oto-cchi...

780
00:49:59,570 --> 00:50:02,300
Konno accepted me for who I am.

781
00:50:02,300 --> 00:50:07,120
The ignorant, useless, worthless me.

782
00:50:07,120 --> 00:50:10,210
She never belittled or made fun of me.

783
00:50:12,110 --> 00:50:14,440
Are rich people really that great?

784
00:50:14,440 --> 00:50:16,440
Who do you think C5 are?

785
00:50:16,440 --> 00:50:18,180
And Eitoku Academy?

786
00:50:18,180 --> 00:50:20,130
I would've left that place a long time ago if I could!

787
00:50:20,130 --> 00:50:23,990
It's the worst school around, filled with ice-cold people.

788
00:50:25,550 --> 00:50:28,910
You're always sticking your nose up at others from up on your perch.

789
00:50:28,910 --> 00:50:31,210
And cutting ties with the weak.

790
00:50:33,690 --> 00:50:36,240
You're really hopeless.

791
00:50:49,160 --> 00:50:51,430
Don't ever talk to me again.

792
00:50:53,320 --> 00:50:55,270
Leave me alone!

793
00:51:00,660 --> 00:51:02,610
Thank you very much.

794
00:51:06,700 --> 00:51:07,960
Let's go home, Konno.

795
00:51:07,960 --> 00:51:10,250
Oh, Oto-cchi!

796
00:51:11,530 --> 00:51:14,060
Why did this happen?

797
00:51:14,060 --> 00:51:16,360
This isn't how I planned it out...

798
00:51:19,370 --> 00:51:22,280
What's this meat?

799
00:51:22,280 --> 00:51:24,100
It's so tender.

800
00:51:24,100 --> 00:51:28,540
Such a magical garden!

801
00:51:28,540 --> 00:51:30,050
Oh?

802
00:51:30,860 --> 00:51:33,790
Now I feel like gifting you something, too.

803
00:51:33,790 --> 00:51:45,120
♪ So you were my prince on a white horse ♪

804
00:51:45,690 --> 00:51:48,000
Prince Haruto.

805
00:51:48,000 --> 00:51:50,050
I've been enchanted by you.

806
00:51:50,050 --> 00:51:52,750
That's how it was supposed to play out.

807
00:51:52,750 --> 00:51:55,650
You're really hopeless.

808
00:51:55,650 --> 00:51:57,680
Why?

809
00:51:57,680 --> 00:52:00,060
Why's she looking at me like that?

810
00:52:01,730 --> 00:52:02,960
Sorry.

811
00:52:02,960 --> 00:52:05,630
You got dumped because of me.

812
00:52:06,530 --> 00:52:07,970
Huh?

813
00:52:07,970 --> 00:52:09,620
I'm really sorry.

814
00:52:09,620 --> 00:52:13,450
I'll at least try to smooth the situation with Oto-cchi for you.

815
00:52:13,450 --> 00:52:14,820
Hey, you commoner.

816
00:52:14,820 --> 00:52:16,060
Huh?

817
00:52:16,060 --> 00:52:18,350
What are you blabbing on about?

818
00:52:18,350 --> 00:52:22,400
You like Oto-cchi, right?

819
00:52:22,400 --> 00:52:24,780
- Huh?!
- Wait, you don't?

820
00:52:24,780 --> 00:52:27,370
Obviously not!

821
00:52:27,370 --> 00:52:30,720
That's the last misunderstanding I need!

822
00:52:30,720 --> 00:52:32,830
I'm going to launch that woman to no-man's land!

823
00:52:32,830 --> 00:52:36,340
Can I get this all to-go?

824
00:52:55,970 --> 00:52:58,420
Please stop the car.

825
00:52:58,420 --> 00:53:00,200
Tenma?

826
00:53:00,200 --> 00:53:01,890
Sorry.

827
00:53:01,890 --> 00:53:04,290
Can you head home without me?

828
00:53:09,930 --> 00:53:12,890
What in the world am I doing?

829
00:53:18,530 --> 00:53:23,360
You reject me and yet you're out at this time of night?

830
00:53:23,360 --> 00:53:24,700
Mr. Maeno.

831
00:53:24,700 --> 00:53:26,870
I have to go.

832
00:53:26,870 --> 00:53:29,550
You rude bitch.

833
00:53:29,550 --> 00:53:31,410
Stop!

834
00:53:31,410 --> 00:53:33,090
How dare you make a fool out of me.

835
00:53:33,090 --> 00:53:35,640
I see you having fun without me!

836
00:53:35,640 --> 00:53:37,630
Stop that!

837
00:53:46,010 --> 00:53:47,050
Why?

838
00:53:47,050 --> 00:53:49,270
Don't get the wrong idea.

839
00:53:49,270 --> 00:53:50,460
What the hell's your problem?

840
00:53:50,460 --> 00:53:52,020
Shut up!

841
00:53:52,700 --> 00:53:54,030
Huh?

842
00:53:54,780 --> 00:53:57,010
Behave, you brat.

843
00:53:57,010 --> 00:53:58,330
- Let's go.
- No!

844
00:53:58,330 --> 00:54:00,220
Come on!

845
00:54:05,450 --> 00:54:06,900
Let go of me!

846
00:54:06,900 --> 00:54:08,050
Quit getting ahead of yourself!

847
00:54:08,050 --> 00:54:10,760
How dare you talk to me like that!

848
00:54:10,760 --> 00:54:11,760
Let go!

849
00:54:11,760 --> 00:54:14,650
Commoners should act like commoners!

850
00:54:14,650 --> 00:54:17,380
Ow, ow, ow!

851
00:54:17,380 --> 00:54:19,330
Someone! Please, help!

852
00:54:19,330 --> 00:54:21,310
Don't ever come near her again!

853
00:54:21,310 --> 00:54:23,250
You hear me?!

854
00:54:26,140 --> 00:54:27,310
Okay, okay!

855
00:54:27,310 --> 00:54:29,220
Fine! Just let go!

856
00:54:33,300 --> 00:54:34,980
What's your problem?

857
00:54:42,070 --> 00:54:43,450
Um...

858
00:54:44,380 --> 00:54:49,460
I don't like you, or have any feelings for you at all!

859
00:54:49,460 --> 00:54:52,230
- What?
- Don't get excited just because I saved you.

860
00:54:52,230 --> 00:54:54,120
You pitiful commoner!

861
00:54:54,120 --> 00:54:56,110
What are you talking about?

862
00:54:56,110 --> 00:55:01,220
I said that there's no way I'd fall in love with a commoner!

863
00:55:01,220 --> 00:55:03,090
- Excuse me?
- Listen.

864
00:55:03,090 --> 00:55:04,860
Don't get the wrong idea.

865
00:55:04,860 --> 00:55:06,660
As if I'd get the wrong idea.

866
00:55:06,660 --> 00:55:07,920
- Because...
- Because what?

867
00:55:07,920 --> 00:55:10,610
Because I have a fiancé!

868
00:55:11,520 --> 00:55:13,760
A fiancé?!

869
00:55:17,290 --> 00:55:21,590
W-W-Who's your fiancé?

870
00:55:23,660 --> 00:55:25,490
Well...

871
00:55:37,990 --> 00:55:41,220
Tenma... Hase?

872
00:55:43,440 --> 00:55:45,120
Oto.

873
00:55:55,450 --> 00:55:58,080
What do I do?

874
00:55:58,080 --> 00:56:01,010
You put in your best, and you have your own strengths, too.

875
00:56:01,010 --> 00:56:04,080
The disease that you've caught is love!
[Is this the start of a miracle romance?!]

876
00:56:04,080 --> 00:56:05,740
This is just an ordinary school.
[They sneaked into their rival school?!]

877
00:56:05,740 --> 00:56:07,910
I won't lose to you, for sure.

878
00:56:07,910 --> 00:56:12,100
But my pathetic life has nothing to do with you, right?
